Interface IOrderProcess

All Known Implementing Classes:
BranchManager, Staff
public interface IOrderProcess
Interface for processing and managing orders within a branch.

    Method

  • Method Details

    • processOrders

      void processOrders(Branch branch, int orderID)
      Processes an order based on the given order ID within a branch context. The specific processing logic will be implemented by the class that implements this interface.
      Parameters:
      branch - The branch where the order needs to be processed.
      orderID - The unique identifier of the order to process.

    • viewNewOrders

      void viewNewOrders(Branch branch)
      Displays a list of new orders that have not yet been processed for a given branch.
      Parameters:
      branch - The branch whose new orders are to be displayed.

    • viewOrder

      void viewOrder(Branch branch, int orderID)
      Views the details of a specific order in a branch using the order ID.
      Parameters:
      branch - The branch where the order is located.
      orderID - The unique identifier of the order to view.
